+# Token Cost Benchmark
+
+This benchmark compares Codex working normally against Codex working with
+Entire CLI assistance. It uses paired trials: the same task starts from the same
+commit in both modes, with fresh child `codex exec --json` sessions.
+
+The default pilot is intentionally small:
+
+```bash
+node scripts/token-benchmark.mjs setup
+node scripts/token-benchmark.mjs run --dry-run
+node scripts/token-benchmark.mjs run --execute
+```
+
+Useful overrides:
+
+```bash
+node scripts/token-benchmark.mjs run \
+  --execute \
+  --replicates 3 \
+  --max-revisions 2 \
+  --worker-model gpt-5.5 \
+  --reviewer-model gpt-5.4
+```
+
+Results are written outside the repository by default:
+
+```text
+/Users/goose-guest/Documents/work/planetfall-bench-runs
+```
+
+The primary comparison is worker token cost to accepted output. Reviewer token
+usage is recorded separately as experiment overhead.
